==Funding==

2017: Slock.it raised about $2M in a seed funding round.<ref name=„funding“/>

Additional Information: In 2016, Slock.it created a Decetralized Autonomous Organization (DAO) called „The DAO“, a set of smart contracts operating on the Ethereum Classic blockchain. Investors can send coins to the DAO and later vote on how to allocate the collected funds among several project proposals. The idea of Slock.it was to make a proposal of their Universal Sharing Network/Ethereum Computer project to raise funds in this way. In the initial phase of The DAO, an attacker discovered a security vulnerability in the code and managed to withdraw around 3.5M ETH (~$50M). Consequently, the community decided to recover the lost funds with a hard fork of the blockchain that resulted in the independently operating Ethereum Blockchain (where „The DAO“-attack was made undone) and the Ethereum Classic Blockchain (where the code of „The DAO“ can still be found).<ref name=„historydao“>https://blog.slock.it/the-history-of-the-dao-and-lessons-learned-d06740f8cfa5, accessed on 02.07.2018.</ref>

